							<br class="clear"/>
							<!-- End each blog post -->
							
														
							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/ritaomokha/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/200104144-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/200104144-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Rita Omokha" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/ritaomokha/">Rita Omokha</a></h6>
										Rita Omokha writes about culture, race, politics, and history. She’s the recipient of the Pulitzer Prize's Traveling Fellowship, the Education Writers Association Features Award, and the Society of Professional Journalists Features Award, among other honors and recognitions. She's an adjunct professor at Columbia University’s Graduate School of Journalism. She’s the author of <em>Resist: How a Century of Young Black Activists Shaped America.</em>																			</div>
